{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"So as a fashion designer,"},{"time":2000,"text":"I've always tended to think of materials"},{"time":4000,"text":"something like this,"},{"time":6000,"text":"or this,"},{"time":9000,"text":"or maybe this."},{"time":12000,"text":"But then I met a biologist,"},{"time":15000,"text":"and now I think of materials like this --"},{"time":18000,"text":"green tea, sugar,"},{"time":20000,"text":"a few microbes and a little time."},{"time":23000,"text":"I'm essentially using a kombucha recipe,"},{"time":25000,"text":"which is a symbiotic mix"},{"time":27000,"text":"of bacteria, yeasts and other micro-organisms,"},{"time":30000,"text":"which spin cellulose"},{"time":32000,"text":"in a fermentation process."},{"time":35000,"text":"Over time, these tiny threads"},{"time":37000,"text":"form in the liquid into layers"},{"time":39000,"text":"and produce a mat on the surface."}]},{"cues":[{"time":44000,"text":"So we start by brewing the tea."},{"time":46000,"text":"I brew up to about 30 liters of tea at a time,"},{"time":49000,"text":"and then while it's still hot, add a couple of kilos of sugar."},{"time":52000,"text":"We stir this in until it's completely dissolved"},{"time":55000,"text":"and then pour it into a growth bath."},{"time":57000,"text":"We need to check that the temperature"},{"time":59000,"text":"has cooled to below 30 degrees C."},{"time":62000,"text":"And then we're ready to add the living organism."},{"time":64000,"text":"And along with that, some acetic acid."},{"time":66000,"text":"And once you get this process going,"},{"time":68000,"text":"you can actually recycle"},{"time":70000,"text":"your previous fermented liquid."},{"time":73000,"text":"We need to maintain an optimum temperature for the growth."},{"time":76000,"text":"And I use a heat mat to sit the bath on"},{"time":79000,"text":"and a thermostat to regulate it."},{"time":81000,"text":"And actually, in hot weather, I can just grow it outside."},{"time":84000,"text":"So this is my mini fabric farm."}]},{"cues":[{"time":86000,"text":"After about three days,"},{"time":88000,"text":"the bubbles will appear on the surface of the liquid."},{"time":91000,"text":"So this is telling us that the fermentation is in full swing."},{"time":94000,"text":"And the bacteria are feeding"},{"time":96000,"text":"on the sugar nutrients in the liquid."},{"time":98000,"text":"So they're spinning these tiny nano fibers"},{"time":100000,"text":"of pure cellulose."},{"time":102000,"text":"And they're sticking together, forming layers"},{"time":104000,"text":"and giving us a sheet on the surface."},{"time":106000,"text":"After about two to three weeks,"},{"time":108000,"text":"we're looking at something which is about an inch in thickness."},{"time":111000,"text":"So the bath on the left is after five days,"},{"time":114000,"text":"and on the right, after 10."},{"time":116000,"text":"And this is a static culture."},{"time":118000,"text":"You don't have to do anything to it;"},{"time":120000,"text":"you just literally watch it grow."},{"time":122000,"text":"It doesn't need light."}]},{"cues":[{"time":124000,"text":"And when it's ready to harvest, you take it out of the bath"},{"time":127000,"text":"and you wash it in cold, soapy water."},{"time":129000,"text":"At this point, it's really heavy."},{"time":131000,"text":"It's over 90 percent water,"},{"time":133000,"text":"so we need to let that evaporate."},{"time":135000,"text":"So I spread it out onto a wooden sheet."},{"time":137000,"text":"Again, you can do that outside"},{"time":139000,"text":"and just let it dry in the air."},{"time":141000,"text":"And as it's drying, it's compressing,"},{"time":143000,"text":"so what you're left with, depending on the recipe,"},{"time":145000,"text":"is something that's either"},{"time":147000,"text":"like a really light-weight, transparent paper,"},{"time":149000,"text":"or something which is much more like a flexible vegetable leather."},{"time":153000,"text":"And then you can either cut that out"},{"time":155000,"text":"and sew it conventionally,"},{"time":157000,"text":"or you can use the wet material"},{"time":159000,"text":"to form it around a three-dimensional shape."},{"time":162000,"text":"And as it evaporates,"},{"time":164000,"text":"it will knit itself together, forming seams."}]},{"cues":[{"time":166000,"text":"So the color in this jacket is coming purely from green tea."},{"time":169000,"text":"I guess it also looks a little bit like human skin,"},{"time":171000,"text":"which intrigues me."},{"time":174000,"text":"Since it's organic,"},{"time":176000,"text":"I'm really keen to try and minimize the addition of any chemicals."},{"time":179000,"text":"I can make it change color without using dye"},{"time":182000,"text":"by a process of iron oxidation."},{"time":184000,"text":"Using fruit and vegetable staining,"},{"time":186000,"text":"create organic patterning."},{"time":188000,"text":"And using indigo,"},{"time":190000,"text":"make it anti-microbial."},{"time":192000,"text":"And in fact, cotton"},{"time":194000,"text":"would take up to 18 dips in indigo"},{"time":197000,"text":"to achieve a color this dark."},{"time":199000,"text":"And because of the super-absorbency of this kind of cellulose,"},{"time":202000,"text":"it just takes one, and a really short one at that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":205000,"text":"What I can't yet do is make it water-resistant."},{"time":208000,"text":"So if I was to walk outside in the rain"},{"time":211000,"text":"wearing this dress today,"},{"time":213000,"text":"I would immediately start to absorb"},{"time":215000,"text":"huge amounts of water."},{"time":218000,"text":"The dress would get really heavy,"},{"time":220000,"text":"and eventually the seams would probably fall apart --"},{"time":222000,"text":"leaving me feeling rather naked."},{"time":224000,"text":"Possibly a good performance piece,"},{"time":226000,"text":"but definitely not ideal for everyday wear."},{"time":230000,"text":"What I'm looking for"},{"time":232000,"text":"is a way to give the material"},{"time":234000,"text":"the qualities that I need."},{"time":236000,"text":"So what I want to do is say to a future bug,"},{"time":239000,"text":"\"Spin me a thread."},{"time":241000,"text":"Align it in this direction."},{"time":243000,"text":"Make it hydrophobic."},{"time":245000,"text":"And while you're at it,"},{"time":247000,"text":"just form it around this 3D shape.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":250000,"text":"Bacterial cellulose is actually already being used for wound healing,"},{"time":254000,"text":"and possibly in the future"},{"time":256000,"text":"for biocompatible blood vessels,"},{"time":259000,"text":"possibly even replacement bone tissue."},{"time":261000,"text":"But with synthetic biology,"},{"time":263000,"text":"we can actually imagine engineering this bacterium"},{"time":267000,"text":"to produce something"},{"time":269000,"text":"that gives us the quality,"},{"time":271000,"text":"quantity and shape"},{"time":273000,"text":"of material that we desire."},{"time":275000,"text":"Obviously, as a designer, that's really exciting"},{"time":278000,"text":"because then I start to think, wow,"},{"time":280000,"text":"we could actually imagine"},{"time":282000,"text":"growing consumable products."}]},{"cues":[{"time":286000,"text":"What excites me about using microbes"},{"time":289000,"text":"is their efficiency."},{"time":291000,"text":"So we only grow what we need."},{"time":293000,"text":"There's no waste."},{"time":295000,"text":"And in fact, we could make it from a waste stream --"},{"time":298000,"text":"so for example,"},{"time":300000,"text":"a waste sugar stream"},{"time":302000,"text":"from a food processing plant."},{"time":304000,"text":"Finally, at the end of use, we could biodegrade it naturally"},{"time":307000,"text":"along with your vegetable peelings."},{"time":310000,"text":"What I'm not suggesting is that microbial cellulose"},{"time":313000,"text":"is going to be a replacement"},{"time":315000,"text":"for cotton, leather or other textile materials."},{"time":318000,"text":"But I do think it could be quite a smart and sustainable addition"},{"time":322000,"text":"to our increasingly precious natural resources."}]},{"cues":[{"time":325000,"text":"Ultimately, maybe it won't even be fashion"},{"time":327000,"text":"where we see these microbes have their impact."},{"time":329000,"text":"We could, for example, imagine"},{"time":331000,"text":"growing a lamp, a chair,"},{"time":334000,"text":"a car or maybe even a house."},{"time":337000,"text":"So I guess what my question to you is:"},{"time":340000,"text":"in the future, what would you choose to grow?"},{"time":342000,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":344000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":353000,"text":"Bruno Giussani: Suzanne, just a curiosity,"},{"time":355000,"text":"what you're wearing is not random. (Suzanne Lee: No.)"},{"time":358000,"text":"This is one of the jackets you grew?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":360000,"text":"SL: Yes, it is."},{"time":362000,"text":"It's probably -- part of the project's still in process"},{"time":364000,"text":"because this one"},{"time":366000,"text":"is actually biodegrading in front of your eyes."},{"time":368000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":370000,"text":"It's absorbing my sweat, and it's feeding on it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":373000,"text":"BG: Okay, so we'll let you go and save it, and rescue it."},{"time":375000,"text":"Suzanne Lee. (SL: Thank you.)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":378000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}